[WHO defines a zoonosis as an infection "shared in nature by man and
animals." This is simple and elegant and implies that there is no
need to coin terms to define the direction of infection. However, for
the sake of clarity, the term "reverse zoonoses" has sometimes been
applied for diseases of humans that infect animals. Such could also
be the case if/when the event in red squirrels described above is
confirmed as resulting from human vectors. - Mod.AS]

[The Isle of Wight and Jersey can be located via the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the UK at
<http://healthmap.org/r/01Je>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
